current problems:

quote removal is ok (manually parse the str after expansion)

filenames with quotes:
	if not introduced via globs, minishell would reject it anyway
	if introduced via globs:
		bash would inject a backslash so that it keeps track
		we do not do backslashes
		...my parser keeps track of which quotes to not consider anyway, and globbing such files would work
	we can stick quote removal with globbing as an either or action

env expansion mostly ok (but I have to traverse quotes manually)
	envs that expand into quotes will behave inconsistently, no good fix
		export a=\"
		./minishell
		"$a" >> """ >> fucked
		"b$a" >> "b"" >> fucked
